    "causal_summary": "Phase 016's research confirmed two real gaps in the phase-011 `mk-deep-loop-guard.js` plugin: (1) it has no mechanism to detect loop-like repeated `orchestrate`-to-command-owned-loop-executor dispatches within a session (phase 012's benchmark measured GPT-5.5 inconsistently refusing one direct dispatch while allowing an identical one); (2) its existing mode-mismatch check resolves the dispatch target via `registry.get(args.subagenttype)`, but `orchestrate.md`'s own dispatch convention sets `subagenttype: \"general\"` on every Task call (independently re-verified against `orchestrate.md`'s real",
